    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So its more complex than that.\n\nCurrently we use jsdelivr /0/ so there's always a version on this endpoint. It may not be the latest one we want but at least there's one\n\nWhile if we use a specific version then it NEEDS to be on jsdelivr once we update gh-pages, which may or may not be the case and will do more harm than good.\n\nStick with the current way for now, let's see if we have issues at any moment.\n\nThe solution will be to use a specific version AND decorelate the gh-pages update from the new version release. (so no more gh pages in release.sh, wait for jsdelivr to pull us)\n",
